(131, 1, 'post', '{\"_token\":\"cSTdC4hPrANcgqrh3X1QmgxYqAhuvS1Bi3RQI9gY\",\"name\":\"Invest Hotel Scheme\",\"slug\":\"invest-hotel-scheme\",\"slug_id\":\"69\",\"model\":\"Botble\\\\Blog\\\\Models\\\\Post\",\"description\":\"Invest Hotel Scheme has been designed to enable property developers to sell hotel rooms, villas, suites or any other part of a hotel to individual buyers.\\r\\n\\r\\nWhile this scheme paves the way to facilitate the overall financing of new hotel projects, it offers individual buyers all the facilities of an exquisitely-furnished new luxury resort hotel.\",\"is_featured\":\"1\",\"content\":\"<p><strong>The project&rsquo;s approbation<\\/strong><br class=\\\"autobr\\\" \\/>\\r\\nA project under the IHS scheme must absolutely be approved by the Board of Investment. Once approved, an IHS certificate will be issued by the promoting company for the construction of an hotel, which rooms, villas, apartments or suites and others may be sold individually in units.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>The Lands&rsquo; surface areas<\\/strong><br class=\\\"autobr\\\" \\/>\\r\\nA hospitality project under the HIS scheme may be developed either on a fully owned land or on a leased land. The land must however extend on an area exceeding one hectare.<br class=\\\"autobr\\\" \\/>\\r\\n<br class=\\\"autobr\\\" \\/>\\r\\n<strong>The selling criteria<\\/strong><br class=\\\"autobr\\\" \\/>\\r\\nThe units or other parts of the hotel may be sols<br class=\\\"autobr\\\" \\/>\\r\\n&bull; On plan<br class=\\\"autobr\\\" \\/>\\r\\n&bull; During the construction phase<br class=\\\"autobr\\\" \\/>\\r\\n&bull; Once the construction phase completed<br class=\\\"autobr\\\" \\/>\\r\\nThe buyer shall receive during the sale, his title deed regarding the unit or the part he paid for.<br class=\\\"autobr\\\" \\/>\\r\\nThe definition and the management of the units or other parts of the hotel are managed by the &ldquo;R&egrave;glements de copropri&eacute;t&eacute;&rsquo; which in his turn is managed by the Mauritian Civil Code.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>IHS PRICES<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>There is no minimum required investment for the acquisition of a room, a suite or other part of a hotel<br class=\\\"autobr\\\" \\/>\\r\\nA minimum investment of $ 500 000 for the acquisition of an individual villa<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The registration fees for the IHS units are calculated at 5% of the selling price in the case of a room&rsquo;s acquisition, suite or other part of the hotel.<br class=\\\"autobr\\\" \\/>\\r\\nFor individual villas, the registration fees are of 70 000 USD (approximately 52 000 Euros).<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align: center;\\\">&nbsp;<img alt=\\\"\\\" src=\\\"https:\\/\\/flex-home.botble.com\\/storage\\/properties\\/32223-43914-378.png\\\" style=\\\"width: 573px; height: 533px;\\\" \\/><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align: center;\\\"><em>hotels, villas, suites, high rise tourist residence accomodations and attractions<\\/em><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Selling an IHS property<\\/strong><br class=\\\"autobr\\\" \\/>\\r\\nAn IHS unit is sold either on plan or during the construction phase or once the construction is achieved. In case of sale on plan, the sale is concluded according to the Vente en l&rsquo;&eacute;tat future d&rsquo;ach&egrave;vement (VEFA) issued by the the Mauritian Civil Code.<br class=\\\"autobr\\\" \\/>\\r\\n<br class=\\\"autobr\\\" \\/>\\r\\n<strong>Who can acquire an IHS in Mauritius? <\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul class=\\\"spip\\\">\\r\\n\\t<li>A Mauritian citizen<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>A foreign citizen<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>A company incorporated in Mauritius<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>A company registered as a foreign company under the Companies Act 2001<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>A company (partnership) registered with the Registrar of Companies<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>A trust administrated by a trustee having a license delivered by the Financial Service Commission<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Important<\\/strong>: A society holding a Global Business Licence issued by the Financial Services Act 2007 may, under no circumstances buy a residential unit under the IHS scheme.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Applicable Conditions<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul class=\\\"spip\\\">\\r\\n\\t<li>The investing amount for an individual villa must compulsorily exceed 500 000 USD (370 000 Euros), taxes including<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>There is no minimum price for the acquisition of a room, suite or other part of the hotel<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>When a unit or any other part of the hotel is subject to an acquisition from a non-Mauritian citizen, or in the case of a society having a non-Mauritian shareholder or if it is a trust which beneficiary is a non-Mauritian citizen, or if the business partner is non-Mauritian, the payment shall be effectuate either in Mauritian Rupees, USD, Euros or Pound Sterling or any other convertible currency.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>In case of payment effectuate in currencies other than USD, the Board of Investment will use the sales exchange rate prevailing on the date of the application to calculate the equivalent in USD and to ensure that the price exceeds 500 000 USD in the case of individual villas<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>In case of a unit&rsquo;s acquisition or any other part of an hotel by a non-Mauritian citizen, the investment shall be financed by the buyer from funds outside Mauritius and transferred through a renowned bank listed in the Banking Almanach approved by the Bank of Mauritius<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>A non-Mauritian Citizen may contract a bank loan in Mauritian Rupees providing that the first 500 000 USD (370 000 Euros) are paid in a convertible foreign currency and that the loan&rsquo;s repayment is effectuate in a convertible foreign currency.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>How to Acquire under IHS<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<div class=\\\"box spip-content-text\\\" itemprop=\\\"articleBody\\\">\\r\\n<ul class=\\\"spip\\\">\\r\\n\\t<li>A foreign citizen, a Mauritian citizen, a company or a trust wishing to buy an IHS in Mauritius must submit an application to the Board of Investment<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Each application including non-refundable registration fees amounting Rs 10 000 payable through the IHS promoter and by check addressed to the Board of Investment director<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>An application is judge receivable and ready to be treated by the Board of Investment after the later received all the information, modalities and documents and as soon as they are considered complete by the BOI.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>In the case of an acquisition by a foreign citizen, the following documents are compulsory:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul class=\\\"spip\\\">\\r\\n\\t<li>Authentic copies of the 5 first pages of his\\/her passport<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Authentic birth certificate<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Morality certificate not older than three months<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>A letter from the bank certifying the buyer&rsquo;s KYC (Know Your Client) exercise.<br class=\\\"autobr\\\" \\/>\\r\\n\\t<br class=\\\"autobr\\\" \\/>\\r\\n\\t<strong>Sale and lease-back<\\/strong><br class=\\\"autobr\\\" \\/>\\r\\n\\tAfter the acquisition of a unit, the owner must conclude a deal allowing the IHS promoter to rent the property.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Use of the hotel room<\\/strong><br class=\\\"autobr\\\" \\/>\\r\\nThe units rented by the IHS promoter may be used and occupied by the owner or any other person authorized by the later for a period not exceeding 45 days on a period of 12 months<br class=\\\"autobr\\\" \\/>\\r\\n<br class=\\\"autobr\\\" \\/>\\r\\n<strong>Hotel operators and management <\\/strong><br class=\\\"autobr\\\" \\/>\\r\\nThe companies operating under the IHS scheme must retain the services of a hotel operator with competences acceptable by the Board of Investment. An IHS must hold a licence from the Tourism Authority to operate.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>The reselling or the transfer of a unit or any other part of a hotel<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul class=\\\"spip\\\">\\r\\n\\t<li>The owner of an IHS property is authorized to re-sell his property without a minimum pricing.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>In the case where the owner of an IHS property wishes to sell or transfer his property, he is to serve a written notice the General Director, at least 30 days before the sale. A copy of the advice will have to be addressed to the IHS Company and to the trustee.\\r\\n\\t<ul class=\\\"spip\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>The sale or the transfer of the property will have to be effectuate to:<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>A Mauritian Citizen<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>A foreign Citizen<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>A company incorporated in Mauritius<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>A company registered as foreign company under the Companies Act 2001<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>A company (partnership) registered with the Registrar of Companies<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t\\t<li>A trust administrated a trustee detaining a license delivered by the Financial Service Commission<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\t<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>The person acquiring the property will have to submit an application according to the following conditions : The application will have to be accompanied by an account opening certification through which shall transmit the IHS unit&rsquo;s payment as well as the check representing the non refundable registration fees amounting Rs 10 000 issued to the Board of Investment.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Next Steps to Acquire under the scheme<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul class=\\\"spip\\\">\\r\\n\\t<li>Privilege IHS renown promoters who proved their worth in the industry with an excellent portfolio of realised projects<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Look for properties according to your criteria on secured and reliable real-estate portals who propose IHS units commercialization<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Unite all the information and details about projects you are interested in.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Carry a study of the project specificities (ask to the promoters their mission statements)<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Try a comparative market study\\/ feasibility project by going through the existing IHS projects offers already commercialised, in commercialisation course or upcoming<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Familiarize yourself with the prevailing Mauritian rupee exchange rate.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Contact the Board of Investment for any information regarding the acquisition of an IHS property in Mauritian<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Participate in themed forums and inquire with those who already invested in IHS properties<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Call your trusted realtor now.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"seo_meta\":{\"seo_title\":null,\"seo_description\":null},\"submit\":\"save\",\"language\":\"en_US\",\"ref_from\":null,\"status\":\"published\",\"format_type\":null,\"categories\":[\"8\"],\"image\":\"properties\\/download.jpeg\",\"tag\":null}', 'updated', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10.14; rv:73.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/73.0', '196.20.218.102', 1, 8, 'Invest Hotel Scheme', 'primary', '2020-03-25 03:49:05', '2020-03-25 03:49:05'),
